title: Grateful Dead Live at Henry J. Kaiser Convention Center on 1987-03-01
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > R8Brain > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 03/2016
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Grey-> Little Red Rooster, Peggy-O, Me & My Uncle, Mexicali Blues, When Push Comes To Shove, It's All Over Now, Row Jimmy-> Let It Grow

Set 2

Hell In A Bucket-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Samson & Delilah, Black Muddy River-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Space-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text:
another XXXcelent recording little play on words with the XXX cellent wording from the opening of 2nd set . these were the Xtasy days at the Kaiser's. There seemed to be a lot of very pure X back then, If I recall correctly it had just become illegal the summer before or maybe summer of 87 I forget.
 About the recording here it is outstanding as is next nights copy from this taper. I thank you very much cause these are my touring days when I did not miss any shows. So to have the memory's come alive like this puts a big grin on my face . Thank you for your continued work getting these recordings up.
